# Linux System Administration Lab

## Overview
Hands-on lab focused on Linux system administration, user management, and service configuration.

## Key Tasks
- Created and managed users and groups
- Configured file permissions and ownership
- Managed system services (SSH, Apache, Samba)
- Implemented scheduled tasks using cron jobs
- Monitored system processes and performance (htop)

## Tools & Technologies
- Linux (Kali / Ubuntu)
- Bash
- Cron
- Systemctl / Services

## Skills Demonstrated
- Linux administration
- System configuration and troubleshooting
- Process and service management
- Automation with cron jobs
